########################################################
# AutoSoC
# Linux
########################################################

This folders is intended to contains all a build of Linux for the AutoSoC. 
Currently, it contains a sample of linux image and the configuration files used to build it.
The sample linux image can be used in RTL Simulation. It boots the kernel and load a sample initramfs to the memory.

To simulate the sample Linux, set the file 'sample_linux/vmlinux-sample' in the xrunPlusArgs.f simulation configuration file.
For more information about the simulation check the Simulation folder.

###############################
Original Repositories
###############################
The Linux repository used is available in the OpenRISC community.
The configuration files used for building the sample linux image are in config_files folder.
The sample linux to be used in simulation is inside the sample_linux folder.

Original repositories can be found in:
Linux: https://github.com/openrisc/linux

Tutorial on Linux: https://github.com/openrisc/tutorials/blob/master/docs/Linux.md
